 The price for 93 octane will increase with 99 cents and 95 octane with R1.00 pushing the general petrol price up to R17 per litre.
The diesel price will increase with R1.24 per litre leaving fuel prices at its highest yet. The increases are said to be a result of general International crude oil prices and a turbulent exchange rate. The filling stations in Middelburg ensured that they have enough supply to fit the demand. Middelburg residents have started filling up their tanks since yesterday in an attempt to avoid long queues, ahead of the midnight increase on Tuesday. Mr de Ridder from the Kanonkop Engen filling station and Ms Botha from Sasol, told www.mobserver.co.za that they took preemptive measures to ensure enough stock for the high demand.  R10 000 reward for information ‘We should kill him’ – Truck driver hears how hijackers argue about his fate #TrafficUpdate: Avoid N4 near Machadodorp VIDEO: Machadodorp two granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za